<s2>
<ptxt>Remove the 16 bolts and the transaxle housing.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="D026384" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Remove the differential assembly.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C134922" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
<s-1 id="RM0000018KO00FX_01_0007" proc-id="RM0250U___00000UD00000">
<ptxt>INSTALL FRONT DIFFERENTIAL RING GEAR</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<s2>
<ptxt>Using ATF and a heater, heat the front differential ring gear to 90 to 110°C (194.0 to 230.0°F).</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="D025215E04" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<atten3>
<ptxt>Do not overheat the ring gear over 110°C (230.0°F).</ptxt>
</atten3>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Clean the contact surface of the front differential case.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Align the matchmarks, and install the front differential ring gear case quickly.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C134908E01" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<atten3>
<ptxt>Do not install the bolts while the ring gear is hot.</ptxt>
</atten3>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Tighten the 10 bolts.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C134909E01" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<torque>
<torqueitem>
<t-value1>95</t-value1>
<t-value2>970</t-value2>
<t-value4>70</t-value4>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<atten3>
<ptxt>Tighten the bolts a little at a time in diagonal order.</ptxt>
</atten3>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
<s-1 id="RM0000018KO00FX_01_0008" proc-id="RM0250U___00000UE00000">
<ptxt>INSTALL TRANSAXLE HOUSING OIL SEAL</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<s2>
<ptxt>Using SST and a hammer, drive in a new oil seal.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="D026451E01" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<sst>
<sstitem>
<s-number>09608-32010</s-number>
</sstitem>
<sstitem>
<s-number>09950-70010</s-number>
<s-subnumber>09951-07150</s-subnumber>
</sstitem>
</sst>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Coat the lip of the oil seal with a small amount of MP grease.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Oil seal drive in depth</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt> -0.5 to 0.5 mm (-0.0197 to 0.0197 in.)</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
<s-1 id="RM0000018KO00FX_01_0009" proc-id="RM0250U___00000UF00000">
<ptxt>INSTALL DIFFERENTIAL SIDE BEARING RETAINER OIL SEAL</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<s2>
<ptxt>Using SST and a hammer, drive in a new oil seal.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C134923E01" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<sst>
<sstitem>
<s-number>09726-36010</s-number>
</sstitem>
<sstitem>
<s-number>09950-70010</s-number>
<s-subnumber>09951-07150</s-subnumber>
</sstitem>
</sst>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Coat the lip of the oil seal with a small amount of MP grease.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Oil seal drive in depth</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt> -0.5 to 0.5 mm (-0.0197 to 0.0197 in.)</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
</subpara>
</para>
